cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modeling and parsing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses probabilistic models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing. It may also be relevant to cs.SD (Sound) as it mentions speech recognition, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are commonly used in language modeling.
